  "couName": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-compression-bending",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-predicts-f1717-noncannulated",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/model/fea-pedicle-screw-noncannulated",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-bench-n11-lab1",
    "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-bench-n11-lab2"
  ],
  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": true,
  "sensitivityAnalysisRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/sensitivity/cou1-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Parametric sensitivity of FEA QoIs to material and contact inputs",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analysis was performed varying cortical bone elastic modulus (±15%), UHMWPE end-cap friction coefficient (0.1–0.4), and titanium alloy yield strength (±10%) against the three primary QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement). Stiffness showed the highest sensitivity to bone modulus (normalised sensitivity index 0.62), while yield force was most sensitive to titanium yield strength (index 0.54); friction coefficient influence on all QoIs remained below 0.15, supporting the nominal contact assumption used in the validated model."
  },
  "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4044760",
